title: 33 Pushup Variations (ALL LEVELS!)

transcript:
What's up, guys? Jeff Cavaliere, ATHLEANX.com. The pushup is by far one of the most classic
exercises of all time, but it's also the one exercise with probably the most variations
of any other exercise. Today I'm going to cover 33 of those from
beginner, to intermediate, to advanced with the idea being this: find the version that
challenges you. If you're still doing the same, old, classic
pushup because that's what you're good at then you're not going to be challenging your
body to get any stronger, any better, any different than it is today. Find the version that challenges you and let's
get this thing done. So there you have it, guys. 33 pushups. Lots to pick from. No excuses, right? The bottom line is this: the way you do the
pushup can challenge you in many, many different ways. You can work on your power. You can work on your strength. You can work on your coordination. You can work on your endurance. There are many, many ways to work a pushup
into your routine. It's choosing the right one and knowing how
to challenge yourself with it. If you're looking for a program that puts
it all together, that challenges you at the right time and makes sure that you're never
getting complacent with where you are right now; then head to ATHLEANX.com and get our
ATHLEANX training system. In the meantime, if you've found this video
helpful, leave your comments and thumbs up below. Let me know what else you want to see here
and I'll do my best to do that for you in the days and weeks ahead. See you, guys!
